----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
=> Exponentiation in Modular Arithmetic

if      a ≡ b(mod N)                                    if      16 ≡ 1 (mod 3) 
then, a^k ≡ b^k(mod N)                                  then  16^5 ≡ 1^5 (mod 3)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-> Exponentiation in Modular Arithmetic : proof

if      a ≡ b(mod N)                                   =>a = N*k + b 
then, a^k ≡ b^k(mod N) 

a^k = (N*k + b)^k
    = (A + b)^k
    = C(k,0)A^k * b^0 + C(k,1)A^k-1 * b^1...+C(k,k)*b^k

a^k ≡ b^k(mod N)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Let's solve some problems

Find 29^10(mod 3)

29 ≡ 2 (mod 3)
(2^10)%10 = (1024)%3
(7)%3 = 1

Find 2^123456789(mod 7)

123456789 ≡ 0 (mod 3)
2^123456789 = (2^3)^41152263
              (8^41152263)%mod 7
          8 ≡ 1 (mod 7)
            = (1^41152263)%7
            = 1     